WHITE RIVER &#8211; One lane of the R40 towards Hazyview has been reopened to traffic, after being closed earlier due to a truck catching on fire.Spokesman for the Department of Community Safety, Security and Liaison, Joseph Mabuza, confirmed that traffic was being regulated and the fire being extinguished.&nbsp;BREAKING NEWS: R40 closed by Da Gama Dam10:15 &#8211; The R40 has been closed due to a truck burning on the road between White River and Hazyview.The road has been closed and motorists are requested to use the R538 if travelling in that direction.Lowvelder will update you as more information becomes available.Motorists are requested to use the R538 in the mean time until the road is opened again